<subsection xml:id="subsec-2-5-6-neg-quant" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Negating Quantifiers</title>


    <p>It is also important to note what the negation of each of these quantifiers is.</p>
    
    <p>
      <alert>Negating an Existential:</alert>
    </p>
  
    <p>
      <idx><h>quantifier</h><h>negation</h></idx>
    <idx><h>negating quantifiers</h></idx>
    <idx><h>exists</h><h>negation</h></idx>
      <me>\sim[\exists x\text{ }P(x)] </me> read literally says, "There does not exist." 
      Sometimes it is helpful to read this as "everybody doesn't." That is <me>\sim[\exists x\text{ }P(x)]\equiv [\forall x\text{ }(\sim P(x))]</me>
    </p>
    <p>
      <alert>Negating a Universal:</alert>
    </p>
    <p>
      <idx><h>quantifier</h><h>negation</h></idx>
    <idx><h>negating quantifiers</h></idx>
    <idx><h>for all</h><h>negation</h></idx>
      <me>\sim [\forall x\text{ }P(x)] </me> says "not all," which can be thought of as, "somebody does." That is,
      <me>\sim[\forall x\text{ }P(x)]\equiv \exists x\text{ }(\sim P(x))</me>
    </p>

    <p></p>
    <example>
    <idx><h>quantifier</h><h>negation</h></idx>
    <idx><h>negating quantifiers</h></idx>
    <idx><h>for all</h><h>negation</h></idx>
    <idx><h>exists</h><h>negation</h></idx>
      <p>For these examples we will see multiple ways to write them.</p>
      <ol>
        <li> 
          <p>
            <m>\sim (\forall n\in \mathbb{Z}</m>  <m>\sqrt{n} \in \mathbb{Z})\equiv (\exists n\in \mathbb{Z}</m>  <m>\sqrt{n} \not\in \mathbb{Z})</m>
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>*NOT* (For all integers <m>n</m>, <m>\sqrt{n}</m> is an integer)</li>
            <li>For some integers <m>n</m>, <m>\sqrt{n}</m> is not an integer.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>\sim (\exists n \in \mathbb{Z}</m>  <m>n^2 =5)\equiv[\forall n \in \mathbb{Z}</m>  <m>n^2 \neq 5]</m>
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>*NOT*(There exists an integer <m>n</m> such that <m>n^2 =5</m>)</li>
            <li>For all integers <m>n</m>, <m>n^2</m> does not equal <m>5</m>.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </example>

</subsection>